-- Germany’s Altmaier Supports Nuclear Phase-Out, Bild Reports
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2012-05-17T17:28:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-17/germany-s-altmaier-supports-nuclear-phase-out-bild-reports.html
Designated German Environment
Minister  Peter Altmaier  said he’s committed to the country’s
long-term phase-out of nuclear energy,  Bild  newspaper reported,
citing an interview.  “The energy transformation is a central government
project,” the newspaper quoted Altmaier as saying in an e-
mailed preview of an interview to be published tomorrow. “I
look forward to leading it to success.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  